body:
Go 1.18 introduced platform variants [for amd64](https://go.dev/wiki/MinimumRequirements#amd64) (example: `linux/amd64/v2`). As far as I know, this lines up with [microarchitecture levels](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86-64#Microarchitecture_levels) defined by Linux distributions.

As such, it would be great if we could ship containers optimized for a specific microarchitecture, where the container platform detects the correct image to use. Right now, the detected platform is always "linux/amd64", which causes only the fallback image to be used instead of an optimized one when using an image manifest like this:

```json
    [{
      "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json",
      "digest": "sha256:a70b99317ded05d4bc9dfcf218c47c5376a24dc38c29676be971f1ce6eb449b0",
      "size": 1249,
      "platform": {
        "architecture": "amd64",
        "os": "linux",
        "variant": "v3"
      }
    },
    {
      "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json",
      "digest": "sha256:e82466228ba672a78d80391d1d7863512ed6688db4c1490c3220536372086e32",
      "size": 1249,
      "platform": {
        "architecture": "amd64",
        "os": "linux",
        "variant": "v2"
      }
    },
    {
      "mediaType": "application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json",
      "digest": "sha256:59c4b481a2bfd500cee1e97e4fe2cdaa5dfdc9575404e7384c62661763c52cb8",
      "size": 1249,
      "platform": {
        "architecture": "amd64",
        "os": "linux"
      }
    }]
```

Could we add the required logic to detect the support microarchitecture to [image/internal/pkg/platform/platform_matcher.go](https://github.com/containers/container-libs/blob/main/image/internal/pkg/platform/platform_matcher.go)?
